1
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:20,708
When did you get
a boyfriend, Akane?

2
00:00:20,791 --> 00:00:22,791
Miu just messaged
me about it, so--

3
00:00:22,875 --> 00:00:24,166
Why Miu?

4
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:26,958
Oh, we were in the same
class a few years ago.

5
00:00:27,041 --> 00:00:28,375
--News gets around.
--Man...

6
00:00:28,458 --> 00:00:30,291
Yeah, well, it must be
if I'm starting to get

7
00:00:30,375 --> 00:00:31,416
messages about it.

8
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,333
Geez, school check-in
will be rough.

9
00:00:33,416 --> 00:00:35,333
[CHINATSU] You're gonna
get so much attention.

10
00:00:35,416 --> 00:00:36,458
[AOI]
It's next week right?

11
00:00:36,541 --> 00:00:37,583
August 19th?

12
00:00:37,666 --> 00:00:39,333
[CHINATSU]
Yep, it sure is.

13
00:00:39,416 --> 00:00:41,875
[AOI]
Ugh. School is such a pain.

14
00:00:45,416 --> 00:00:47,375
[taiko drums playing]

15
00:01:12,916 --> 00:01:14,708
Right, let's take a break.

16
00:01:31,416 --> 00:01:32,500
[KOTAROU sighs]

17
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:37,458
[KOTAROU]
Dazai once said,

18
00:01:37,541 --> 00:01:40,125
"There is such a thing
as love in this world.

19
00:01:40,208 --> 00:01:41,833
I'm sure of it.

20
00:01:41,916 --> 00:01:44,958
It's the expression
and the etiquette

21
00:01:45,041 --> 00:01:46,875
that makes love
so hard to find."

22
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:30,208
Whoa, seriously? No way!

23
00:03:30,291 --> 00:03:32,666
It's true. Azumi and
Mizuno are a thing now.

24
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:34,041
Jeez, crazy!

25
00:03:34,125 --> 00:03:35,125
I know, right?

26
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:36,333
No fair.

27
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:38,208
--I'm so jealous.
--He's so lucky.

28
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:45,250
[ROMAN laughs]

29
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:46,625
Kota! You're famous!

30
00:03:46,708 --> 00:03:47,750
Well hey, you little player!

31
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:49,000
[ROMAN, DAICHI laugh]

32
00:03:49,083 --> 00:03:51,083
[DAICHI] How dare you go
and get a girlfriend?

33
00:03:51,166 --> 00:03:52,416
Way to go, tiger!

34
00:03:57,083 --> 00:03:58,625
--Hey.
--[AIRA] You're here!

35
00:03:58,708 --> 00:03:59,666
Hey!

36
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:01,000
[AIRA]
Come on!

37
00:04:01,083 --> 00:04:01,833
[AKANE]
Why?

38
00:04:01,916 --> 00:04:03,416
[MIU]
Ugh, just come on!

39
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,625
So what's the deal, Akane?

40
00:04:07,708 --> 00:04:08,833
[AKANE]
With what?

41
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:10,083
Why'd you pick Azumi?

42
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:12,125
Jeez, Miu, talk about rude!

43
00:04:12,208 --> 00:04:13,458
It's not rude!

44
00:04:13,541 --> 00:04:15,208
Just kind of surprised, is all.

45
00:04:15,291 --> 00:04:16,083
Sorry.

46
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:17,875
What is it you like about him?

47
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:19,833
Well, uh...

48
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:23,583
[SETSUKO laughs]
Nothing?

49
00:04:23,666 --> 00:04:25,875
[AIRA]
Well, there has to be something.

50
00:04:25,958 --> 00:04:27,375
It's hard to describe.

51
00:04:28,625 --> 00:04:29,916
Know what I mean?

52
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,208
[GIRLS]
Huh?

53
00:04:31,291 --> 00:04:32,833
You do like him, right?

54
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:37,416
I seriously thought
you'd end up with Hira.

55
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,666
--[SETSUKO] Me too.
--[AIRA] For real.

56
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:42,000
Well, no more secrets, okay?

57
00:04:42,083 --> 00:04:43,083
'Kay.

58
00:04:43,166 --> 00:04:45,208
Let us know if he kisses you.

59
00:04:45,291 --> 00:04:47,041
Do you think he
could actually do it?

60
00:04:47,125 --> 00:04:48,166
[AIRA]
No!

61
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:51,583
[GIRLS laugh]

62
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:53,416
If you're already done
with your summer homework,

63
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:55,833
go ahead and put it on my desk.

64
00:04:55,916 --> 00:04:57,708
We're already halfway
through the summer break,

65
00:04:57,791 --> 00:04:59,166
so if you haven't
finished your work,

66
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:00,750
then you need to get on it.

67
00:05:17,125 --> 00:05:18,750
[STUDENTS chattering]

68
00:05:29,541 --> 00:05:30,750
You going home together?

69
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:31,833
She has club.

70
00:05:31,916 --> 00:05:33,458
So wait for her, then!

71
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:35,125
You have club too, right?

72
00:05:35,208 --> 00:05:36,208
[ROMAN]
Mm-hmm.

73
00:05:36,291 --> 00:05:37,291
[KOTAROU gasps]

74
00:05:47,875 --> 00:05:48,875
[KOTAROU]
Mizuno!

75
00:05:57,958 --> 00:06:01,250
I have club, so why don't
we walk home together?

76
00:06:14,083 --> 00:06:15,041
[chuckles]

77
00:06:22,208 --> 00:06:25,458
[TRACK TEAM 8A]
Get ready, set, go!

78
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:34,958
[AOI]
It's hot today.

79
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:37,375
[CHINATSU]
I'm literally starving.

80
00:06:37,458 --> 00:06:38,625
[AOI]
Let's go get some food then.

81
00:06:38,708 --> 00:06:40,041
[CHINATSU]
Let's get ice cream!

82
00:06:40,125 --> 00:06:41,583
[AOI]
That sounds pretty tempting.

83
00:06:41,666 --> 00:06:42,875
--Which shop?
--[CHINATSU] Let me think.

84
00:06:42,958 --> 00:06:45,958
[AKANE]
Sorry, guys, it's just...

85
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:47,250
Got plans?

86
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:48,125
[AKANE]
Mm-hmm.

87
00:06:48,208 --> 00:06:49,333
With Azumi?

88
00:06:52,041 --> 00:06:53,041
Well, have fun.

89
00:06:53,125 --> 00:06:54,125
Later.

90
00:07:01,541 --> 00:07:03,333
[CHINATSU]
She's so lucky.

91
00:07:03,416 --> 00:07:05,208
[AOI] Why? Boyfriends
are such a hassle.

92
00:07:05,291 --> 00:07:06,208
[CHINATSU]
Huh?

93
00:07:06,291 --> 00:07:07,791
[AOI]
I don't get the appeal.

94
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:19,875
Hi, Akane.

95
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:23,958
Akane.

96
00:07:58,666 --> 00:08:00,375
--Thank you for the food.
--Thank you for the food.

97
00:08:08,625 --> 00:08:10,708
Ah! That hits the spot!

98
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:12,416
You sound like my dad.

99
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:14,458
Whatever, it's hot.

100
00:08:14,541 --> 00:08:15,708
How's your club going?

101
00:08:15,791 --> 00:08:17,541
Awesome, just busy.

102
00:08:17,625 --> 00:08:19,166
I can only imagine.

103
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:20,083
What about you?

104
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:21,291
We're kinda lax.

105
00:08:22,875 --> 00:08:24,791
[KOTAROU] But I'm busy with
summer lessons and the festival.

106
00:08:24,875 --> 00:08:26,500
Ah, cram school?

107
00:08:26,583 --> 00:08:28,083
Uh-huh.

108
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:30,291
[AKANE] I guess I should start
going once track season is over.

109
00:08:30,375 --> 00:08:31,250
Oh, in the fall?

110
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:32,291
[AKANE]
Yeah.

111
00:08:34,583 --> 00:08:35,666
Just a sec.

112
00:08:41,208 --> 00:08:42,375
What's up?

113
00:08:42,458 --> 00:08:44,041
[KOTAROU]
They want me to come practice.

114
00:08:44,125 --> 00:08:45,000
Drum practice?

115
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:45,833
[KOTAROU]
Yep.

116
00:08:45,916 --> 00:08:47,083
I wanna see!

117
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:50,083
Can I come watch?

118
00:08:50,166 --> 00:08:51,208
[KOTAROU]
Sure, I guess.

119
00:08:51,291 --> 00:08:52,333
Yay, cool!

120
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,875
Oh, would it bother you?

121
00:08:56,958 --> 00:08:58,291
Not at all!

122
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:03,125
[AKANE laughs]

123
00:09:11,125 --> 00:09:13,166
[DAISUKE]
Let's take it from the top.

124
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:14,208
[KOTAROU]
Right.

125
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:15,875
This is unusual.

126
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:17,083
So, who might you be?

127
00:09:17,166 --> 00:09:18,666
Hello, there.
It's nice to meet you.

128
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:20,000
Oh, it's Kotarou's girl--

129
00:09:20,083 --> 00:09:20,833
Shut up!

130
00:09:20,916 --> 00:09:22,583
His girlfriend?

131
00:09:22,666 --> 00:09:24,166
I see!

132
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:26,375
Way to go, champ! [laughs]

133
00:09:26,458 --> 00:09:27,416
Here.

134
00:09:30,166 --> 00:09:31,583
[KOTAROU]
You can sit here.

135
00:09:31,666 --> 00:09:33,208
Thanks so much.

136
00:09:33,291 --> 00:09:35,291
[taiko drums playing]

137
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:37,375
[music continues]

138
00:10:34,791 --> 00:10:35,958
[DAISUKE]
How was it?

139
00:10:36,041 --> 00:10:36,958
[AKANE]
Amazing!

140
00:10:37,041 --> 00:10:38,625
I'd never seen it before.

141
00:10:38,708 --> 00:10:40,333
I absolutely loved watching.

142
00:10:40,416 --> 00:10:42,166
[DAISUKE]
Good to hear.

143
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:44,083
I hope we didn't
intrude on a date.

144
00:10:44,166 --> 00:10:45,791
What? Nah.

145
00:10:45,875 --> 00:10:46,625
Oh.

146
00:10:46,708 --> 00:10:48,291
Have you seen Hikawa Shrine?

147
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:49,416
Uh...

148
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,125
[DAISUKE]
The, uh, wind chimes are up.

149
00:10:51,208 --> 00:10:53,541
Oh. That sounds cool.

150
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:55,208
[DAISUKE]
It is.

151
00:10:55,291 --> 00:10:56,250
Huh?

152
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:58,916
Azumi.

153
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,125
Here, take this.

154
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:02,416
But...

155
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,416
Just take it.

156
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,958
Wait, are you sure?

157
00:11:05,041 --> 00:11:07,125
How about I finish
up things here?

158
00:11:27,083 --> 00:11:28,125
[AKANE]
Sorry I'm late.

159
00:11:28,208 --> 00:11:29,166
[KOTAROU]
Huh?

160
00:11:42,083 --> 00:11:44,125
[AKANE] I told my mom
we were going to a festival

161
00:11:44,208 --> 00:11:46,541
and she made me put it on.

162
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:47,583
[KOTAROU]
Ah.

163
00:11:49,666 --> 00:11:51,875
So uh, how's it look?

164
00:11:51,958 --> 00:11:53,666
It looks amazing.

165
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:54,875
So do you.

166
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:57,875
Thank you.

167
00:12:04,083 --> 00:12:07,166
[AKANE] It's cool how
everything is potato themed.

168
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:08,958
I know, right? They're famous.

169
00:12:09,041 --> 00:12:10,041
Interesting!

170
00:12:11,625 --> 00:12:12,958
It's delicious!

171
00:12:13,041 --> 00:12:14,500
We eat them a lot at my house.

172
00:12:14,583 --> 00:12:15,791
Lucky.

173
00:12:15,875 --> 00:12:17,416
Actually, when I was
younger I didn't like them

174
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:19,166
very much.

175
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:20,625
But now they're really good.

176
00:12:25,291 --> 00:12:26,291
[AKANE chuckles]

177
00:12:29,916 --> 00:12:32,083
No way! I have one of these.

178
00:12:33,791 --> 00:12:36,291
Feel one. They're super
soft and squishy.

179
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:38,916
[KOTAROU chuckles]
You're right.

180
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,000
Now I want one!

181
00:12:40,083 --> 00:12:41,333
[BOTH laugh]

182
00:12:44,291 --> 00:12:45,333
[AKANE]
Look over here!

183
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:48,500
Everything's so cute!

184
00:12:50,875 --> 00:12:53,375
I've always loved
more traditional styles.

185
00:12:53,458 --> 00:12:54,416
Yeah?

186
00:12:56,041 --> 00:12:57,125
It suits you.

187
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:07,083
[KOTAROU]
Fortunes?

188
00:13:07,166 --> 00:13:08,875
[AKANE]
When's your birthday?

189
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:11,041
[KOTAROU]
Oh. It's August 7th.

190
00:13:11,125 --> 00:13:12,000
[AKANE gasps]

191
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:13,083
We missed it?

192
00:13:13,166 --> 00:13:14,208
[KOTAROU]
Hey, no big deal.

193
00:13:14,291 --> 00:13:15,250
Yes, it is!

194
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:16,375
I'm not upset.

195
00:13:16,458 --> 00:13:17,500
[AKANE]
Well, I am.

196
00:13:19,625 --> 00:13:21,625
But I didn't know about it.

197
00:13:21,708 --> 00:13:24,291
I would have liked
to celebrate together.

198
00:13:24,375 --> 00:13:26,041
Seriously, it's fine.

199
00:13:26,125 --> 00:13:27,166
I feel bad.

200
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:28,416
Honestly, I'm used to it

201
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:31,416
since it's during
summer break and all.

202
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:32,791
[AKANE]
I guess.

203
00:13:32,875 --> 00:13:34,750
Excuse me,
I need to go call home.

204
00:13:34,833 --> 00:13:35,833
[KOTAROU]
Right now?

205
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:55,250
So pricey.

206
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:12,250
[AKANE]
Okay, I'm back.

207
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:13,458
All done, then?

208
00:14:17,416 --> 00:14:18,375
[AKANE]
Yeah.

209
00:14:19,750 --> 00:14:20,791
Ready to go?

210
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:48,375
[AKANE]
They're beautiful!

211
00:14:48,458 --> 00:14:50,125
I've never been here before.

212
00:14:50,208 --> 00:14:51,708
Oh, wow. Seriously?

213
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:52,750
Yeah.

214
00:15:16,541 --> 00:15:19,000
[AKANE] Apparently you can
write wishes on the chimes!

215
00:15:24,416 --> 00:15:25,583
I'll take two, please.

216
00:15:25,666 --> 00:15:27,250
[SHOP CLERK 8A]
That'll be 1000 yen.

217
00:15:38,041 --> 00:15:39,875
What's your wish?

218
00:15:39,958 --> 00:15:42,083
Sorry, I'm not telling.

219
00:15:42,166 --> 00:15:43,750
It's embarrassing.

220
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:13,791
Wanna keep going?

221
00:16:13,875 --> 00:16:14,833
Yeah.

222
00:16:17,666 --> 00:16:18,666
[KOTAROU]
What's wrong?

223
00:16:19,791 --> 00:16:21,500
Sorry, hold on.

224
00:16:25,541 --> 00:16:26,833
I need a minute.

225
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:36,708
[KOTAROU]
Let me.

226
00:16:45,291 --> 00:16:46,291
[KOTAROU]
There.

227
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:50,041
[AKANE]
Um, thank you.

228
00:16:50,125 --> 00:16:51,750
Shall we, then?

229
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:53,333
Uh, hang on!

230
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,208
Here.

231
00:16:58,291 --> 00:17:00,125
It's a belated birthday present.

232
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:03,291
Thank you!

233
00:17:04,375 --> 00:17:05,333
[AKANE]
Open it!

234
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:12,583
[KOTAROU chuckles]

235
00:17:12,666 --> 00:17:14,583
[AKANE] Sorry,
I didn't have time to choose,

236
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:16,666
so it looks just like mine.

237
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:18,750
Don't apologize, I love it.

238
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,791
Wait a minute,
did you buy this earlier?

239
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,000
[AKANE]
Uh, yeah.

240
00:17:25,083 --> 00:17:26,500
It's so awesome.

241
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,250
[AKANE]
I'm so glad.

242
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:33,500
I wasn't even sure when
I should give it to you

243
00:17:33,583 --> 00:17:35,125
or if you'd even like it.

244
00:17:35,208 --> 00:17:37,708
I couldn't stop thinking
about it, you know?

245
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:39,750
[AKANE sighs]
I was so nervous,

246
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:41,250
even when we were
looking at wind chimes,

247
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:43,250
my heart was pounding.

248
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:44,916
I'm so happy you like it.

249
00:17:51,291 --> 00:17:55,083
Um, well, thanks
so much, Akane.

250
00:17:58,625 --> 00:17:59,833
Uh, I--

251
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:05,041
[AKANE]
It's okay, Kotarou.

252
00:18:07,125 --> 00:18:09,250
[KOTAROU laughs]

253
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:16,000
[SETSUKO] I don't think I've
ever seen you and Azumi

254
00:19:16,083 --> 00:19:17,583
talk during class.

255
00:19:17,666 --> 00:19:18,958
Yeah, he's a quiet guy.

256
00:19:19,041 --> 00:19:22,250
Come on, Akane,
what is it you like about him?

257
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:25,166
I know Azumi might not
seem like much to you,

258
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:27,166
but I feel safe around him.

259
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:28,666
Aww!

260
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,000
You're different these days.

261
00:19:30,083 --> 00:19:31,833
Well, they say love
can change a person.

262
00:19:31,916 --> 00:19:33,458
[AIRA]
Have you kissed? Tell us!

263
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:35,333
[MIU]
No secrets, remember?

264
00:21:44,625 --> 00:21:46,000
Hey. I've heard of that girl.

265
00:21:46,083 --> 00:21:47,500
Yeah? Who is she?

266
00:21:47,583 --> 00:21:49,041
She's like a new idol.

